## Available Base Stacks

### Core

**DHCP**
Full name: "ETH>IP>UDP>DHCP"
Description: DHCP server for IP address assignment
Example: "Start a DHCP server on interface eth0"
Startup parameters: None

**DNS**
Full name: "ETH>IP>UDP>DNS"
Description: Domain name resolution server
Example: "DNS server on port 53 and resolve everything to 93.184.216.34"
Startup parameters: None

**DataLink**
Full name: "ETH"
Description: Layer 2 Ethernet frame server
Example: "Listen on eth0 via Ethernet"
Startup parameters:
  • interface (required) - Network interface name to capture packets from (e.g., 'eth0', 'en0', 'wlan0')
    Example: "eth0"
  • filter (optional) - Optional BPF (Berkeley Packet Filter) expression to filter captured packets (e.g., 'arp', 'tcp port 80')
    Example: "arp"

**DoH**
Full name: "ETH>IP>TCP>TLS>HTTP2>DNS"
Description: DNS-over-HTTPS server for secure domain resolution
Example: "DNS-over-HTTPS server on port 443 resolving all queries to 93.184.216.34"
Startup parameters: None

**DoT**
Full name: "ETH>IP>TCP>TLS>DNS"
Description: DNS-over-TLS server for secure domain resolution
Example: "DNS-over-TLS server on port 853 resolving all queries to 93.184.216.34"
Startup parameters: None

**HTTP**
Full name: "ETH>IP>TCP>HTTP"
Description: Web server serving HTTP traffic
Example: "Pretend to be a sassy HTTP server on port 8080 serving cooking recipes"
Startup parameters: None

**NTP**
Full name: "ETH>IP>UDP>NTP"
Description: Network Time Protocol server for time synchronization
Example: "pretend to be a ntp server on port 123"
Startup parameters: None

**SNMP**
Full name: "ETH>IP>UDP>SNMP"
Description: SNMP agent for network monitoring
Example: "SNMP Port 8161 serve OID 1.3.6.1.2.1.1.1.0 (sysDescr) return 'NetGet SNMP Server v0.1'"
Startup parameters: None

**SSH**
Full name: "ETH>IP>TCP>SSH"
Description: Secure shell server for remote access
Example: "Pretent to be a shell via SSH on port 2222"
Startup parameters:
  • send_first (optional) - Whether the server should send the first message after connection (not typically needed for this protocol)
    Example: false

**TCP**
Full name: "ETH>IP>TCP"
Description: Raw TCP socket server for custom protocols
Example: "Pretend to be FTP server on port 2121; serve file accounts.csv with 'balance,0'"
Startup parameters:
  • send_first (optional) - Whether the server should send the first message after connection (e.g., for FTP/SMTP greeting banners)
    Example: false

**UDP**
Full name: "ETH>IP>UDP"
Description: UDP datagram server
Example: "Listen on port 5000 via UDP"
Startup parameters: None

